---
title: Skillet Chilaquiles with Black Beans, Pickled Radish and Sour Cream
description: Chilaquiles is Mexican comfort food at its finest. Traditionally, a pile of fried tortillas is topped with spicy sauces, plenty of cheese, and even fried eggs. Our version takes advantage of fiery abodo sauce in a deliciously smoky black bean topping. A sprinkle of crisp radish salad and cheddar cheese will make this a dish you won’t want to share!
